track_notes:
Take NM Hwy 9 west out of Santa Teresa. Proceed to the intersection of Hwy 9 and County Road A-005. Turn right on A-005 and proceed north. Pass through the ranch and continue north.  At the major Y intersection, stay to the left.  When you see Cox Peak out the right side, watch for a dim 2-track going in to the base of the summit.  Take that 2-track until it ends at the wash. Park.

Cross the wash, stay left of the first small hill. Continue up the arroyo until you see the spur due south of your position.  Climb up that spur headed south, then turn east and eventually north-east until you reach the summit.
